FBIS3-36653 "drsov026_a_94032" FBIS-SOV-94-026 Document Type:Daily Report 8 Feb 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Detained Boats To Be Escorted Out LD0802075594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0723 GMT 8 Feb 94 LD0802075594 Moscow ITAR-TASS Language: English Article Type:BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Yevgeniy Belovitskiy] [Text] Yuzhno-Sakhalinsk February 8 TASS -- Japanese fishing boats "Kai-Ei-Maru-58" and "Kini-Maru-53" detained on February 7 for illegal fishing in Russian territorial waters are waiting near the island on Kunashir until the weather clears up. The Japanese boats are being guarded by a Russian border guard ship. The Japanese boats will be convoyed to the Krabozavodskaya Bay as soon as the storm subsides, ITAR-TASS learned from the press service of Russian border guard troops.
